The paper proposes a novel framework for multi-task reinforcement learning using variational inference formulation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of policies as a space of skills for hierarchical reinforcement learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of latent-space embeddings, which is a common technique in Computer Vision (cs.CV), suggesting that it may also belong to this sub-category.
